  "text": "Among the very few approaches dealing with calendar information embedded in documents, we can first mention [CITATION_1] , which developed a temporal search engine supporting a Web search on temporal information embedded in Web pages. Secondly, and the closest to our approach, we can mention [CITATION_2] which proposes a search engine capturing calendar information in documents. Their goal is to build clusters of documents and then rank documents in each cluster according to the calendar information that the documents contain. Like the other experimentations mentioned, they do not provide a means to express queries containing a Calendar Expression. In this sense, expressiveness is limited.",
